  "text": "Recently, an index comprising routinely available laboratory tests was developed for the assessment of liver fibrosis in CHC patients, namely the aspartate aminotransferase to platelet ratio index (APRI). [CITATION_1] For bridging fibrosis and cirrhosis, the proposed APRI cutoff values are > 1.5 and > 2, respectively, with areas under the receiver operating curve (ROC) of 0.80 and 0.89.",
